For 161, the first project is publically available. You could find the second and third specs online but not the autograders. The third project changes a lot but recently has been CTF-style web exploiting that you can find all over the internet. I don't know if there would be much online material for something like the 2nd project though.

I have no idea about the hws for 161 but they generally aren't super long so it wouldn't be a core part of the class.

history.content:
TA for 161 here - the first and third projects are publicly available (it's self-explanatory whether you've completed the project, the autograder is just there to verify for completion and detect cheating). The second project is heavily design-based and open-ended and the autograder is not public, even for students, so I doubt you'll be able to self-grade project 2.

The hw is generally exam-level conceptual questions, we don't release the solutions publicly but you can get a similar learning experience by doing the past midterms.

As for 186 (which I don't TA for but have taken before), the projects have a mix of public tests (bundled with the code, which I think is publicly available) and hidden autograder tests (which are not public even for students), so you can work on projects up to the point where all the public tests pass (which anecdotally speaking is a good indicator you've passed most of the hidden tests too).

TA for 161 here - the first and third projects are publicly available (it's self-explanatory whether you've completed the project, the autograder is just there to verify for completion and detect cheating). The second project is heavily design-based and open-ended and the autograder is not public, even for students, so I doubt you'll be able to self-grade project 2.

The hw is generally exam-level conceptual questions, we don't release the solutions publicly but you can get a similar learning experience by doing the past midterms.

I really want to take both of these classes in order to build a really strong SWE foundation, but unfortunately may not have the bandwidth before I graduate (In preference for courses like 126, 127, 128, 106a which may be harder to self-learn).

One reason why I tend to enjoy classes more than self learning is because of the projects and constant assignments, especially given the depth at which Cal classes are taught. I was wondering if the assignments and grading for these two classes are publicly available, so that if I wanted to do a project or homework I can see if I passed all the cases or not. 

If these tests aren't available for people not enrolled to use, are there other courses or resources one could use to get as good of an understanding and experience on security and databases that these classes offer?
history.subject: how self-learnable is the material taught in 161 and 186?
